   <h1>The Troll&#39;s Bane Chronicle</h1>

   <h2>The fifth year of the new era: July</h2>

<p> In the 5th year of the new age on July 1st, the dwarf Durin Silberbart is announced as the official Purveyor of the Grey Rose for smithed goods. </p>
<p> In the 5th year of the new age on July 4th, Josephine announces with the letter on the town wall that she will leave the island. </p>
<p> In the 5th year of the new age on July 5th, Lord Aristeaus of Varshikar asks Lennier of the Grey Rose for a meeting on neutral soil. </p>
<p> In the 5th year of the new age on July 5th, Lennier asks the town why they are so unenthusiastic when it comes to the future of the Trollsbane. He is met with little interest. </p>
<p> In the 5th year of the new age on July 6th, the druid Caitlin Fergus offers to train five people to become medicos for the health of the city. </p>
<p> In the 5th year of the new age on July 6th, Aristeaus announces a new alliance with Tol Vanima. He withdraws his wife Quinasa from official tasks. </p>
<p> In the 5th year of the new age on July 7th, Lennier announces that all Varshikaris that enter Trollsbane must pay a tax of 250 copper coins. Arguments soon erupt between both cities and disputes over land soon emerge. </p>
<p> In the 5th year of the new age on July 10th, town guard Kamik Windslasher reports the murder of the Dwarf Balin Lightaxe; he asks if anyone has information about the name 'Rasmantil'. </p>
<p> In the 5th year of the new age on July 11th, the elf Misjbar asks the Elven community whether they would like a new leader. </p>
<p> In the 5th year of the new age on July 12th, the Elf Landury Bringard asks for a teacher to teach him the art of smithing. Salathe is recommended. </p>
<p> In the 5th year of the new age on July 14th, a message appears in town claiming that demons are attacking. </p>
<p> In the 5th year of the new age on July 14th, Julius of Greywolf announces the death of the Dwarf Galim; he announces Galim was killed by a Demon. </p>
<p> In the 5th year of the new age on July 16th, Durin Silberbart announces that the funerals of both Galim and Balin Lightaxe will be rescheduled to the 9th Ronas. </p>
<p> In the 5th year of the new age on July 16th, Gwynnether von Glanwen sends a message to the pirate Gerard, challenging him to a duel in retaliation to Galim's Death. </p>
<p> In the 5th year of the new age on July 16th, The Dwarf Sylvia Ironpick offers a reward for Durin Silberbart's head. Durin soon retaliates and asks citizens to attack Sylvia </p>
<p> In the 5th year of the new age on July 16th, a man calling himself 'The Master', announces the formation of his guild 'The knighthood of Ringeil. No more is heard from him. </p>
<p> In the 5th year of the new age on July 18th, Caitlin Fergus announces that, should she be absent or be killed Alysha Eisenhauer will lead her guild 'The Druids of the Forest.' </p>
<p> In the 5th year of the new age on July 18th, Greenbriar announces the completion of a new Onion ball field. </p>
<p> In the 5th year of the new age on July 19th, The Salkaemarian Markous announces that he has maps to sell for a small payment. </p>
<p> In the 5th year of the new age on July 21st, Misjbar Mehialho forms 'The Synode,' a guild he promises will become more powerful than the 'Grey Rose'. </p>
<p> In the 5th year of the new age on July 23rd, Lennier asks citizens why the town has become infested with weeds and plants. It is later discovered that a spirit had taken control of the large Naldor tree in front of the shop, and had caused the environment to spiral out of control with its power. </p>
<p> In the 5th year of the new age on July 24th, Town Guard Callith announces that Kamik Windslasher has been stripped of his title of town guard. He is accused of aiding a prisoner to escape and for murder. </p>
<p> In the 5th year of the new age on July 25th, Town Guard Callith asks the citizens of Trollsbane to pack up and move to the Grey rose castle due to the sudden outburst of plants and other wildlife sealing the town. </p>
<p> In the 5th year of the new age on July 27th, Pendar Fayed, captain of the town guard, accuses the man Anither (also known as 'guider') of the attempted murder of a 13 year old girl, Rhiannon. </p>
<p> In the 5th year of the new age on July 27th, the astrologer Farnistle announces that the current calendar of Gobaith is incorrect and that from the month of Mas, all months will have 24 days. </p>
<p> In the 5th year of the new age on July 28th, a parchment appears in which Maeve offers her services as a fortune teller. </p>
<p> In the 5th year of the new age on July 28th, the dwarf Durin Silberbart denies claims that he plans to take over King Tialdin's throne, quashing many rumours. </p>
<p> In the 5th year of the new age on July 28th, the elf Callith calls on all warriors to unite and help defend Trollsbane from attacking golems. </p>
<p> In the 5th year of the new age on July 29th, the Druids of the Forest offer there help to clear up the overgrown shrubs and leaves that now cover Trollsbane. </p>
<p> In the 5th year of the new age at the end of July, the Halfling Erart Ridoc asks for a tailor. He also asks for samples of their work. </p>


